vvm
===

|Pypi Status| |Build Status| |Coverage Status|

Vyper version management tool.

Installation
------------

via ``pip``
~~~~~~~~~~~

.. code:: bash

   pip install vvm

via ``setuptools``
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

.. code:: bash

   git clone https://github.com/vyperlang/vvm.git
   cd vvm
   python3 setup.py install

Testing
-------

``vvm`` is tested on Linux, OSX and Windows with Vyper versions
``>=0.1.0-beta.16``.

To run the test suite:

.. code:: bash

   pytest tests/

By default, the test suite installs all available ``vyper`` versions for
your OS. If you only wish to test against already installed versions,
include the ``--no-install`` flag. Use the ``--vyper-verions`` flag to
test against one or more specific versions.

